"><mn>86.91</mn></math></span></span></td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"16.7%\"><math alttext=\"16.7%\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>16.7</mn><mo>%</mo></math></span></span></td><td class=\"entry colname:col4\"> stable</td></tr></tbody></table></div><ul class=\"unordered_list style:2\"><li class=\"list_item\"><p class=\"list_paragraph\">(i) Using the values in the table, calculate the average atomic mass, in amu, of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R b\"><math alttext=\"R b\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>Rb</mi></math></span></span> in the sample.</p></li></ul></div>\n","rubricRef":"VR732217_rubric"},{"id":"VR732217","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<div class=\"item_part part_id:cii part_name:ExtendedText response_class:FreeResponse response_type:Essay\" id=\"cii\"><ul class=\"unordered_list style:2\"><li class=\"list_item\"><p class=\"list_paragraph\">(ii) <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R b 83\"><math alttext=\"R b 83\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>Rb</mi><mtext>-</mtext><mn>83</mn></math></span></span> undergoes radioactive decay into gaseous <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"K r 83\"><math alttext=\"K r 83\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>Kr</mi><mtext>-</mtext><mn>83</mn></math></span></span>, which leaves the solid sample. Over time, how will the average atomic mass of the remaining sample compare to the value calculated in part (c)(i) ?</p></li></ul></div>\n","rubricRef":"VR732217_rubric"}]